Executive Profile
Beryl B. Raff  Chairman and Chief Executive Officer, Helzberg Diamond Shops, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 11 different industries.See Board Relationships66--
Background

		Ms. Beryl B. Raff has been the Chief Executive Officer of Helzberg Diamond Shops, Inc., an indirect wholly owned subsidiary of Berkshire Hathaway Inc. since April 2009. Ms. Raff served as Executive Vice President and General Merchandising Manager, Fine Jewelry division at J. C. Penney Company, Inc. since September 22, 2005 until 2009. She was employed at J.C. Penney Company, Inc. since 2001. Ms. Raff served as Chief Executive Officer of Whitehall Jewelers Holdings, Inc. ... from August 12, 2005 to September 8, 2005. She served as Chief Executive Officer at WJ Holdings Liquidating Company since August 2005. Previously, she spent six years with Zale Delaware Inc., a specialty retailer of fine jewelry, advancing to Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and Executive Vice President and spent 19 years with R.H. Macy & Company, a department store retailer, advancing to Senior Vice President/General Merchandising Manager. She served as Chairman of the Board and Chief executive officer of Zale Corporation. During her career at JCPenney, Ms. Raff became the first general merchandise manager to receive the JCPenney Chairman's Award, highest tribute to managerial excellence - an honor she received three times, including this year, 2007. She has been Chairman of the Board of Helzberg Diamond Shops, Inc., since April, 2009. She has been an Independent Director of The Michaels Companies, Inc. since September 23, 2014 and Helzberg Diamond Shops, Inc. since April 2009. She serves as a Director of Michaels Stores, Inc. and Dallas Summer Musicals. She has been an Independent Director of Helen of Troy Limited since August 2014. She served as a Director of Jo-Ann Stores Inc., from 2001 to March 18, 2011. She also serves on numerous jewelry-industry professional boards, including the Jewelers Vigilance Committee and Jewelers Circular Keystone. She served as Director of Zale Corporation. Ms. Raff served as a Director of Group 1 Automotive Inc. from June 25, 2007 to February 20, 2015. She is a past executive board member and vice chairman of the North Texas Chapter of the Make-A-Wish Foundation and continues to work passionately on its behalf. In 1999, the Women's Jewelry Association named her to its Lifetime Hall of Fame and in 2002 the Jewelry Industry Chapter of American ORT presented her with their Community Achievement Award. Ms. Raff is the 1999 and 2006 recipient of the UJA-Federation of New York Diamond, Jewelry and Watch Division's "Leadership Award of Excellence." Ms. Raff received her bachelor of science from Boston University, where she graduated magna cum laude and received her master's of business administration from Drexel University.Read Full Background




